	<Title>
		Office work: Don&apos;t take it sitting down!
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Finding time to exercise can be a challenge for anyone with a busy schedule. Why not work out while you&apos;re at work? Here are five ways to make office exercise part of your routine: 1. Walk or bike to work, get off the bus a few blocks early or park farther from the door. 2. Look for opportunities to stand. Try a standing desk, or improvise with a high table or counter. 3. Trade your office chair for a fitness ball. 4. Organize a lunchtime walking group. 5. Conduct walking meetings.&lt;/p&gt;
